 Summary 
 JOB DESCRIPTION: Geodetic Earth Scientists analyze the Earth's gravity and magnetic fields, geophysical structure, material properties, and dynamics for geospatial intelligence and DoD applications. They define and maintain the World Geodetic System (WGS), perform datum transformations between WGS 84 and local datums, and develop spatial and temporal models defining Earth systems. They provide in-depth technical e 
 
 Responsibilities 
 ADDITIONAL INFORMATION: 1) This position is the Lead SPACE Scientist for Gravity and Magnetic Field Modeling. It is outer space mission focused. The geodetic principles are chiefly the same with application in a space Position, Navigation and Timing (PNT) environment. 
 
2) Geodetic Earth Scientists work in a group or team analyzing the Earth's gravity & magnetic fields, geophysical structure, material properties, & dynamics for geospatial intelligence. They're the DoD and IC focus for Geodesy & Geophysics issues. They develop spatial & temporal models defining Earth systems & demographics. They define & maintain the World Geodetic System (WGS) & its associated models to accurately position geospatial intelligence worldwide in a common reference system. They analyze weapon systems to determine the effects of geodetic quantities on navigation & targeting performance. They provide technical knowledge on Geodetic & Geophysical issues to internal & external customers & attend community forums as necessary
 
 
3) In support of NGA & USSPACECOM national security mission, the Office of Geomatics is seeking to hire a Band 04 Team Lead position. This position will assist in SPACE application, SPACE-based derivative requirements, and SPACE mission assurance. Proficiency in the following scientific areas & processes are required: astrodynamics, reference frame transformations, application & production of gravity & geomagnetic data, developing methodologies, procedures & production in support of SPACE navigation & operations, Earth & SPACE-based collection systems for WGS 84, & data / collection / mission assurance. This position is technical with the acumen to lead a group of geodetic scientists in support of the SPACE mission set. Contributions increase resiliency of national PNT infrastructure while increasing accuracies achievable in global navigation. It improves knowledge & tradecraft necessary to enable Space Situational Awareness, Indications & Warnings, SPACE traffic management in addition to Command & Control, and lastly, SPACE communications & navigation services for spatial requirements. Must understand orbit determination / propagation & the four-dimensional (4-D) SPACE environment of celestial bodies in relation to time / motion variables. This position serves as the Gravity and Magnetic Field modeling expert as it relates to SPACE who applies & produces necessary products in support of the WGS 84, both Earth & SPACE domains, & studies potential applications of geomatics tradecraft, methods & production in a SPACE-based environment. This position leads development & studies of potential courses of action. Ensures mission assurance in all phases of support to near term SPACE operations, & make resource recommendations for application of geomatics production in support of the SPACE mission set. Applicants must exhibit technical knowledge & have the ability to enable healthy partnerships & balance between the mission & employee development. He or she establishes & maintains open / ongoing dialogue with team members, assists with performance expectations for the employee's direct supervisor & establishes a team who upholds to NGA core values; Excellence, Accountability, Respect, Teamwork, Honesty. 
 
This position may be eligible for an INCENTIVE: selected candidates may be offered an incentive as part of the offer of employment, based on budget availability. To receive the incentive, selected candidates must be eligible under 5 CFR Part 575 upon issuance of the Final Offer Letter. Changes in federal employment status prior to issuance of the Final Offer Letter may affect eligibility. Incentive recipients sign a service agreement depending on the approved amount or duration of the incentive. If the employee leaves before the end of the service agreement, the employee may be required to repay a pro rata share amount of the incentive to the government. 
 
